@description.name: @description
@description.body: Transports requests to a server using the native XmlHttpRequest object. This class should not be used directly by client programmers.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Capabilities of this transport type.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Return a new XMLHttpRequest object suitable for the client browser.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Whether the transport type is supported by the client.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The timeout for Xhr requests

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Sets the timeout for requests

@deprecated.name: @deprecated
@deprecated.body:
{6.0} This method is deprecated from the start because synchronous I/O itself is deprecated
  in the W3C spec {@link https://xhr.spec.whatwg.org/} and timeouts are indicative of synchronous I/O and/or
  other server issues.  However, this API is still supported by many browsers and this API is useful
  for code which has not made the transition to asynchronous I/O

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the timeout for requests

@description.name: @description
@description.body: If true and the responseType property is set to "application/json", getResponseContent() will return a Javascript map containing the JSON contents, i. e. the result qx.lang.Json.parse(). If false, the raw string data will be returned and the parsing must be done manually. This is useful for special JSON dialects / extensions which are not supported by qx.lang.Json.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the native request object

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Implementation for sending the request

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Force the transport into the failed state ("failed"). This method should be used only if the requests URI was local access. I.e. it started with "file://".

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Listener method for change of the "readystate". Sets the internal state and informs the transport layer.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Get the ready state of this transports request. For qx.io.remote.transport.XmlHttp, ready state is a number between 1 to 4.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Set a request header to this transports request.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns a specific header provided by the server upon sending a request, with header name determined by the argument headerName. Only available at readyState 3 and 4 universally and in readyState 2 in Gecko. Please note: Some servers/proxies (such as Selenium RC) will capitalize response header names. This is in accordance with RFC 2616[1], which states that HTTP 1.1 header names are case-insensitive, so your application should be case-agnostic when dealing with response headers. [1]RFC 2616: HTTP Message Headers

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns all response headers of the request.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Provides a hash of all response headers.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the current status code of the request if available or -1 if not.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Provides the status text for the current request if available and null otherwise.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Provides the response text from the request when available and null otherwise. By passing true as the "partial" parameter of this method, incomplete data will be made available to the caller.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {String} Content of the response as string
@return.description: Content of the response as string

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Provides the XML provided by the response if any and null otherwise. By passing true as the "partial" parameter of this method, incomplete data will be made available to the caller.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {String} Content of the response as XML
@return.description: Content of the response as XML

@throws.name: @throws
@throws.body: {Error} If an error within the response occurs.
@throws.description: If an error within the response occurs.

@description.name: @description

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the content of the response
